Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with optimizing bandwidth usage in wireless networks, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The use of network coding to optimize caching is a key aspect of the paper, which is a topic covered in this sub-category. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper deals with distributed caching among social groups, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with social groups and their impact on caching, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper deals with optimizing performance in wireless networks through caching, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
